y","text":"navigate","headword":"navigate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 驾驶(to direct the course of a ship or plane); 航行(to follow a planned course"},{"type":"text","text":"['navigert]"},{"type":"text","text":"on, across,or through)：使通过"},{"type":"text","text":"圈词根记忆：nav（船)+ig（走）+ate→驾船走→航行"},{"type":"text","text":"As more people try to navigate the legal system by themselves, representing"}]},{"number":355,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"text","text":"arises whether they will be able to avoid judicial quagmires without lawyers to"},{"type":"text","text":"guide them."},{"type":"entry","text":"celibate","headword":"celibate"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.独身者（an unmarried person) adj.不结婚的"},{"type":"text","text":"['selrbat]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：celib（单个）+ate→独身者"},{"type":"entry","text":"also-ran","headword":"also-ran"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.落选者（a contestant that does not win);不重要的参与者(one that is of little"},{"type":"text","text":"['s:lsauraen]"},{"type":"text","text":"importance)"},{"type":"entry","text":"offstage","headword":"offstage"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj台后的，幕后的(not on the open stage)"},{"type":"text","text":"[:f'sterd3]"},{"type":"text","text":"图组合词：off（离开）+stage（舞台）→离开舞台→台后的"},{"type":"entry","text":"reprimand","headword":"reprimand"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.训l诚，遣责（a severe or formal reproof)v.训l诚，责（to reprove sharply or"},{"type":"text","text":"['reprrmend]"},{"type":"text","text":"censure formally)"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：re（重新）+prim（首要）+（m）and（命令）→再次给以严厉的命令→谜责"},{"type":"entry","text":"grope","headword":"grope"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.摸索，探索(to feel or search about blindly)"},{"type":"text","text":"[graup]"},{"type":"text","text":"圈联想记忆：g（看作grasp.抓住）+rope（绳子）→抓住绳子→摸索，探索"},{"type":"entry","text":"flimsy","headword":"flimsy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 轻而薄的(thin and easily broken or damaged);易损坏的(poorly made and"},{"type":"text","text":"[flimzi]"},{"type":"text","text":"fragile)"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：flim（看作film，胶卷）+sy→像胶卷一样的东西→易损坏的"},{"type":"entry","text":"sacred","headword":"sacred"},{"type":"text","text":"adfj.神圣的，庄严的(holy, inviolable)"},{"type":"text","text":"['serkrid]"},{"type":"text","text":"divine"},{"type":"entry","text":"indecipherable","headword":"indecipherable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 无法破译的(incapable of being deciphered)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rndr'sarfrabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：in（不）+decipher（破解，破译）+able→无法破译的"},{"type":"entry","text":"incompetent","headword":"incompetent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 无能力的，不胜任的(lacking the qualities needed for effective action)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn'ka:mprtant]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：in（不）+competent（有能力的）→无能力的"},{"type":"entry","text":"bashfulness","headword":"bashfulness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 羞怯(shyness, timidity)"},{"type":"text","text":"['bae[flnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自bashful（adj羞怯的，钮妮的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"halting","headword":"halting"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 跨露的，迟疑不决的(marked by hesitation or uncertainty)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ho:Itrn]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自halt（v.停住，停顿）"},{"type":"entry","text":"conquer","headword":"conquer"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 以武力征服(to take possession of sth. by force)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ka:nkar]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：con（加强）+quer（寻求：获得）→全部寻求到→以武力征服"},{"type":"entry","text":"world-beater","headword":"world-beater"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 举世无双的人(a person or thing that is better than all others)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,w3:rld’bi:tar]"},{"type":"entry","text":"short-sightedness","headword":"short-sightedness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.目光短浅(lacking foresight);近视"},{"type":"text","text":"[Jo:rt'sartrdnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"Many elderly people are capable of working. but they are kept from gainful"},{"type":"text","text":"employment by the shorl-sightedness of those employers who mistakenly"},{"type":"text","text":"believe that young people alone can give them adequate service."},{"type":"entry","text":"irresolute","headword":"irresolute"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 末决定的(uncertain how to act or proceed);犹豫不决的(lacking in resolution;"},{"type":"text","text":"[t'rezalu:t]"},{"type":"text","text":"indecisive)"},{"type":"entry","text":"unpromising","headword":"unpromising"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无前途的，没有希望的（not promising)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'pra:misin]"},{"type":"text","text":"不要和uncompromising（adj不妥协的）相混"}]},{"number":356,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 32 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"time-consuming","headword":"time-consuming"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 费时(间的(using or taking up a great deal of time)"},{"type":"text","text":"['tarmkansu:min]"},{"type":"definition","text":"a time-consuming job —项费时的工作"},{"type":"entry","text":"iniquitous","headword":"iniquitous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.邪恶的，不公正的（wicked，unjust)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'nikwitas]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：in（不）+iqu（公正的）+itous→不公正的"},{"type":"entry","text":"unbiased","headword":"unbiased"},{"type":"text","text":"adfj. 没有偏见的(free from all prejudice and favoritism)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'barast]"},{"type":"text","text":"留 The fact that a theory is plausible does not necessarily ensure its scientific"},{"type":"text","text":"truth, which must be established by unbiased controlled studies."},{"type":"entry","text":"self-deprecation","headword":"self-deprecation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 自鸣(self-mockery)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,selfdepra'ker{n]"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparatively few rock musicians are willing to laugh at themselves, although"},{"type":"definition","text":"a hint of self-ceprecation can boost sales of video clips very nicely."},{"type":"entry","text":"autobiographical","headword":"autobiographical"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad自传的，自传体的"},{"type":"text","text":"[:ta,bara'graefikl]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：auto（自己的）+biography（传记）+ical→自传的"},{"type":"entry","text":"indiscriminately","headword":"indiscriminately"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv. 随意地，任意地(in a random manner; promiscuously)"},{"type":"text","text":"[indr'skriminatli]"},{"type":"text","text":"Although most worthwhile criticism concentrates on the positive, one should"},{"type":"text","text":"not indliscriminately praise everything."},{"type":"entry","text":"arbitrarily","headword":"arbitrarily"},{"type":"entry","text":"equation","headword":"equation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.等式；等同，相等（action of making equal)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'kwe13n]"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.没骨气的，偶弱的(lacking courage or willpower)"},{"type":"entry","text":"spineless","headword":"spineless"},{"type":"text","text":"['sparnlas]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：spine（脊椎，刺）+less→无脊椎的→没骨气的"},{"type":"text","text":"Are we to turn into spineless equivocators, afraid to take a forthright stand,"},{"type":"text","text":"unable to answer a question without pussyfooting?"},{"type":"entry","text":"converse","headword":"converse"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan'v3:rs] v. 谈话，交谈(to exchange thoughts and opinions in speech)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka:nv3irs] adj 逆向的(opposite) n. 相反的事物(an opposite)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：con（共同）+vers（转）+e→全部转换方向→逆向的"},{"type":"entry","text":"overinflated","headword":"overinflated"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj过度充气的（filled with too much air)"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvarin'flertid]"},{"type":"text","text":"Like a balloon that is overinflated, aneurysms sometimes enlarge so much"},{"type":"text","text":"that they burst."},{"type":"entry","text":"cold-blooded","headword":"cold-blooded"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj冷血的：残酷的(without pity)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kauld'bladid]"},{"type":"entry","text":"damped","headword":"damped"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.潮湿的：减震的，压低（声音）的"},{"type":"text","text":"[dampt]"},{"type":"entry","text":"ancestral","headword":"ancestral"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 祖先的,祖传的(of, relating to, or inherited from an ancestor)"},{"type":"text","text":"[en'sestral]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：an（加强）+cest(看作cess，行走）+ral→走了很久的→祖先的"},{"type":"entry","text":"demagnetize","headword":"demagnetize"},{"type":"text","text":".消磁，使退磁(to deprive of magnetic properties)"}]},{"number":357,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"dehumanize","headword":"dehumanize"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 使失掉人性(to deprive of human qualities, personality, or spirit)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,di:'hju:manarz]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：de（除去）+humanize（使人性化)→使失掉人性"},{"type":"entry","text":"illiterate","headword":"illiterate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj文盲的(ignorant,uneducated)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'litarat]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：i（不）+literate（识字的）→不识字的→文盲的"},{"type":"entry","text":"ferocity","headword":"ferocity"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 凶猛，残暴(the quality or state of being ferocious)"},{"type":"text","text":"[fa'ra:sati]"},{"type":"text","text":"fierceness, furiousness, vehemence, wildness"},{"type":"entry","text":"snobbery","headword":"snobbery"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.势利（snobbish conduct or character)"},{"type":"text","text":"['sna:bari]"},{"type":"entry","text":"bilateral","headword":"bilateral"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 两边的(having two sides); 双边的(affecting reciprocally two nations or"},{"type":"text","text":"[,bar'laetaral]"},{"type":"text","text":"parties)"},{"type":"entry","text":"unscented","headword":"unscented"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj无气味的（without scent)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'sentid]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：un（不）+scented（有气味的）→无气味的"},{"type":"entry","text":"opalescent","headword":"opalescent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 发乳白色光的(reflecting an iridescent light)"},{"type":"text","text":"[aupa'lesnt]"},{"type":"entry","text":"preferably","headword":"preferably"},{"type":"text","text":"adk更可取地，更好地，宁可"},{"type":"text","text":"['prefrabli]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自prefer（v.宁可，更喜欢）"},{"type":"entry","text":"activate","headword":"activate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.刺激，使活动(to make active or more active)"},{"type":"text","text":"['aektrvert]"},{"type":"text","text":"The burglar alarm is activated by movement."},{"type":"definition","text":"n.极度（the utmost degree)：绝境，险境，临终（a moment marked by imminent"},{"type":"entry","text":"extremity","headword":"extremity"},{"type":"text","text":"[rk'stremati]"},{"type":"text","text":"destruction or death)"},{"type":"entry","text":"successively","headword":"successively"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.接连地，继续地(in proper order or sequence)"},{"type":"text","text":"[sak'sesivli]"},{"type":"text","text":"Not all the indicators necessary to convey the effect of depth in a picture work"},{"type":"text","text":"simultaneously: the picture's illusion of uniform three-dimensional appearance"},{"type":"text","text":"must therefore result from the viewer's integration of various indicators perceived"},{"type":"text","text":"successively."},{"type":"text","text":"consecutively, continuously, uninterruptedly"},{"type":"entry","text":"serrated","headword":"serrated"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.锯齿状的（saw-toothed)"},{"type":"text","text":"[sa'rertid]"},{"type":"text","text":"图 serrated knife/edge 锯齿状刀子/边缘"}]},{"number":358,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 32 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"rocky","headword":"rocky"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj多岩石的(abounding in or consisting of rocks)：坚若磐石的(firmly held)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ra:ki]"},{"type":"entry","text":"compensatory","headword":"compensatory"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.补偿性的，报酬的（compensating)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kam'pensato:ri]"},{"type":"text","text":"He received a compensafory payment of 20,000."},{"type":"entry","text":"dilapidated","headword":"dilapidated"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 破旧的, 双坏的(broken down; shabby and neglected)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dr'lapidertid]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：di（二）+lapid（石头）+ated→（造房的）石头一分为二→毁坏的"},{"type":"entry","text":"touch","headword":"touch"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 涉及(to relate to or have an influence on); 触动(to hurt the feelings of); 接触(to"},{"type":"text","text":"[At]"},{"type":"text","text":"be in contact) n. 触提(a light stroke, tap, or push)"},{"type":"text","text":"Although Henry was not in general a sentimental man, occasionally he would"},{"type":"text","text":"feel a touch of nostalgia for the old days and would contemplate making a brief"},{"type":"text","text":"excursion to Boston to revisit his childhood friends."},{"type":"text","text":"feel, finger"},{"type":"entry","text":"gorgeous","headword":"gorgeous"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 华丽的; 极好的(brilliantly showy; splendid)"},{"type":"text","text":"['go:rd3as]"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：gorge（峡谷）+ous→峡谷是美丽的→华丽的"},{"type":"entry","text":"concurrent","headword":"concurrent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 并发的(operating or occurring at the same time);协作的，—致的(acting in"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan'ks:rant]"},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction)"},{"type":"entry","text":"eventful","headword":"eventful"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.多事的(full of or rich in events);重要的(momentous)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'ventfl]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自event（n.事件）"},{"type":"entry","text":"constructive","headword":"constructive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 建设性生的(promoting improvement or development)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan'strAktrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"constructive suggestions 建设性的提议"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.使某人或某事物敏感（to make.sb./sth.sensitive）"},{"type":"entry","text":"sensitize","headword":"sensitize"},{"type":"text","text":"['sensatarz]"},{"type":"text","text":"过词根记忆：sens（感觉）+itize→使某人或某事物教感"},{"type":"entry","text":"delimit","headword":"delimit"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 定界，划界(to fix the limits of)"},{"type":"text","text":"[di'lxmrt]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：de（使）+limit（界限）→加强限定→划界"},{"type":"entry","text":"impersonate","headword":"impersonate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 模仿(to mimic);: 扮演(to act the part of)"},{"type":"text","text":"[xm'ps:rsanert]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：im（饰以-）+person（人）+ate→饰演别人→扮演"},{"type":"entry","text":"spined","headword":"spined"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj有背骨的，有脊柱的"},{"type":"text","text":"[spaind]"},{"type":"entry","text":"domination","headword":"domination"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.控制，支配，管辖（exercise of mastery or ruling power)"},{"type":"text","text":"[da:mr'nexfn]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：domin（支配）+ation→控制，支配，管辖"},{"type":"entry","text":"unquestioning","headword":"unquestioning"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无异议的，不犹豫的（not questioning)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'kwestfanin]"},{"type":"entry","text":"execute","headword":"execute"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.执行，履行（to carry out)：将(某人）处死(to kil sb.as a legal punishment)"},{"type":"text","text":"['eksikju:t]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：exe（电脑中的可执行文件）+cute→执行，履行"},{"type":"text","text":"Totem craftsmanship reached its apex in the 19th century. when the"},{"type":"text","text":"introduction of metal tools enabled carvers to execute more sophisticated"},{"type":"text","text":"designs."}]},{"number":359,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"truculence","headword":"truculence"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.野蜜，残酷(the quality or state of being truculent)"},{"type":"text","text":"['trakjalans]"},{"type":"text","text":"truculency"},{"type":"entry","text":"enumerate","headword":"enumerate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.列举，枚举（to name one by one)"},{"type":"text","text":"[t'nu:marert]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：e（向外）+numer（数字）+ate→用数字表示出来→列举"},{"type":"entry","text":"typographical","headword":"typographical"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 印别上的(of typography)"},{"type":"text","text":"[tar'pa:grafikl]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自typography（n.印刷术）"},{"type":"text","text":"Because it has no distinct and recognizable typographical form and few"},{"type":"text","text":"recurring narrative conventions, the novel is, of all literary genres, the least"},{"type":"text","text":"susceptible to definition."},{"type":"entry","text":"mythic","headword":"mythic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.神话的：虚构的"},{"type":"text","text":"[mxθrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"legendary, mythical, mythological"},{"type":"entry","text":"penal","headword":"penal"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj惩罚的，刑罚的(of, relating to, or involving punishment, penalties, or punitive"},{"type":"text","text":"['pi:nl]"},{"type":"text","text":"institutions)"},{"type":"entry","text":"bowlegged","headword":"bowlegged"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad弯脚的，弓形腿的"},{"type":"text","text":"[bau'legrd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"rugged","headword":"rugged"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 高低不平的：崎枢的(having a rough uneven surface)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ragid]"},{"type":"text","text":"bumpy, craggy"},{"type":"entry","text":"affront","headword":"affront"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.侮辱，冒犯(to offend)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'frant]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：af（向外）+front（前面，脸面）→冲着别人的脸→冒犯"},{"type":"text","text":"confront, encounter"},{"type":"entry","text":"righteousness","headword":"righteousness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.正当，正义，正直"},{"type":"text","text":"['rartfasnas]"},{"type":"entry","text":"critique","headword":"critique"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 批评性的分析(critical analysis)"},{"type":"text","text":"The book provides a radical cnitique of modern workplace structure."},{"type":"text","text":"[krr'ti:k]"},{"type":"entry","text":"notate","headword":"notate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.以符号表示(to put into notation)"},{"type":"text","text":"[nautrt]"},{"type":"text","text":"圈词根记忆：not（标记）+ate→做标记→以符号表示"},{"type":"entry","text":"blighted","headword":"blighted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.枯菱的(withered)"}]},{"number":360,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 32 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"decisiveness","headword":"decisiveness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.坚决，果断"},{"type":"text","text":"[dt'sarsivnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自decisive（adj坚决的，果断的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"impassable","headword":"impassable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不能通行的，无法通过的(incapable of being passed, traveled, crossed,or"},{"type":"text","text":"[rm'paesabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"surmounted)"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.沼泽的，湿地的(marshy)"},{"type":"entry","text":"swampy","headword":"swampy"},{"type":"text","text":"['swa:mpi]"},{"type":"text","text":"图 swampy lake 沼泽湖泊"},{"type":"entry","text":"mystic","headword":"mystic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 神秘的(having a spiritual meaning or reality that is neither apparent to the"},{"type":"text","text":"['mrstik]"},{"type":"text","text":"senses nor obvious to the intelligence); 谜样的，难解的(enigmatic; obscure)"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.神秘主义者"},{"type":"entry","text":"fortitude","headword":"fortitude"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 坚毅，坚忍不拔(strength of mind that enables a person to encounter danger"},{"type":"text","text":"[fo:rtrtu:d]"},{"type":"text","text":"or bear pain)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：fort（力量；强壮的）+itude（状态）→坚毅"},{"type":"entry","text":"resentful","headword":"resentful"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.愤恨的，怨恨的(full of resentment)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'zentfl]"},{"type":"text","text":"留 indignant"},{"type":"entry","text":"stately","headword":"stately"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 庄严的，堂皇的; 宏伟的(marked by lofty or imposing dignity)"},{"type":"text","text":"['stertli]"},{"type":"text","text":"august, dignified, majestic"},{"type":"entry","text":"postdate","headword":"postdate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 填迟 -的B期(to put a date on (a check, for example) that is later than the"},{"type":"text","text":"['pa:stdert]"},{"type":"text","text":"actual date)"},{"type":"entry","text":"indigence","headword":"indigence"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.贫穷，贫困（poverty:lacking money and goods)"},{"type":"text","text":"['rndidzans]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆联想记忆：in（无）+dig（挖）+ence→挖不出东西→贫穷"},{"type":"text","text":"留 Micawber’'s habit of spending more than he earned left him in a state of"},{"type":"example","text":"perpetual indligence, but he persevered in hoping to see a more afluent day."},{"type":"text","text":"destitution, impecuniousness, impoverishment, penury, privation"},{"type":"entry","text":"hot-tempered","headword":"hot-tempered"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 性急的，易怒的，暴躁的(tending to become very angry easily)"},{"type":"text","text":"[hot'tempard]"},{"type":"entry","text":"collusion","headword":"collusion"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.共谋，勾结（secret agreement or cooperation)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka’lu:3n]"},{"type":"text","text":"collusion with与.勾结"},{"type":"entry","text":"peevish","headword":"peevish"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj不满的，抱怨的（discontented，querulous)：暴躁的，坏脾气的，易怒的"},{"type":"text","text":"[pi:vJ]"},{"type":"text","text":"(fractious, fretful)"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自peeve（v使气恼，使焦躁）"},{"type":"text","text":"Safire as a political commentator is patently never satisfied; he writes peevish"},{"type":"text","text":"editorials about every action the government takes."},{"type":"text","text":"huffy, irritable, pettish"},{"type":"entry","text":"demystify","headword":"demystify"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 减少-的神秘性(to make sth. less mysterious)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,di:'mrstifar]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：de（去掉）+mystify（使迷惑）→去掉迷惑→减少·的神秘性"}]},{"number":361,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"indistinguishable","headword":"indistinguishable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj无法区分的，难以分辨的（notdistinguishable）"},{"type":"text","text":"[xndr'stingw{abl]"},{"type":"text","text":"be indistinguishable from无法从中区分"},{"type":"entry","text":"imbue","headword":"imbue"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.浸染，浸透(to permeate or influence as if by dyeing）：使充满，灌输，激发(to"},{"type":"text","text":"[m'bju:]"},{"type":"text","text":"endow)"},{"type":"entry","text":"astray","headword":"astray"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj迷路的，误入歧途的（off the right path or way)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'strer]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：a（处于）+stray（走离）→走离正道→误入歧途的"},{"type":"entry","text":"adoration","headword":"adoration"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.崇拜，爱慕（the act of adoring)"},{"type":"text","text":"[aeda'rer{n]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自adore（v崇拜）"},{"type":"entry","text":"hydrate","headword":"hydrate"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 水合物 v (使)水合(to cause to take up or combine with water)"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：hydr（水）+ate→水合"},{"type":"text","text":"['hardrert]"},{"type":"entry","text":"operative","headword":"operative"},{"type":"text","text":"adj（计划等）实施中的，运行着的（operating）：生效的（effective）"},{"type":"text","text":"[a:paratrv]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：oper（做)+ative→在做的→实施中的"},{"type":"entry","text":"subdued","headword":"subdued"},{"type":"text","text":"adj（光和声）柔和的，缓和的：（人)温和的(unnaturally or unusually quiet in"},{"type":"text","text":"[sab'du:d]"},{"type":"text","text":"behavior)"},{"type":"entry","text":"reconnaissance","headword":"reconnaissance"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 侦察,预先勘测(a preliminary survey to gain information)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'ka:nisns]"},{"type":"text","text":"图注意不要和renaissance（n.复兴；复活）相混"},{"type":"entry","text":"reenact","headword":"reenact"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 再制定(to enact again)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ril'naekt]"},{"type":"text","text":"To have true disciples, a thinker must not be too idliosyncratic: any effective"},{"type":"text","text":"intellectual leader depends on the ability of other people to reenact thought"},{"type":"text","text":"processes that did not originate with them."},{"type":"entry","text":"self-procession","headword":"self-procession"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.自行列队"},{"type":"text","text":"[,selfpra'se{n]"},{"type":"entry","text":"ingrate","headword":"ingrate"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.忘恩负义的人(an ungrateful person)"},{"type":"text","text":"[in'grert]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：in（不）+grat（令人高兴的）+e→不令人高兴的→忘恩负义的人"},{"type":"entry","text":"underdeveloped","headword":"underdeveloped"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不发达的(not fuilly grown or developed)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Andardr'velapt]"},{"type":"entry","text":"clamber","headword":"clamber"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.吃力地爬上，攀登(to climb awkwardly)"}]},{"number":362,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 32 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"reciprocally","headword":"reciprocally"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.相互地：相反地"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'siprakli]"},{"type":"entry","text":"mutually","headword":"mutually"},{"type":"entry","text":"amicably","headword":"amicably"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv. 友善地(in an amicable manner)"},{"type":"text","text":"['emrkabli]"},{"type":"entry","text":"reparable","headword":"reparable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj能补数的，可挽回的（capable of being repaired)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'perabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自repair（v.修补）"},{"type":"entry","text":"axiom","headword":"axiom"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 公理(maxim): 定理(an established principle)"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：axi有价值）+om→有价值的理论→公理"},{"type":"text","text":"['aeksiam]"},{"type":"entry","text":"undistorted","headword":"undistorted"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad未失真的"},{"type":"text","text":"[Andr'sto:rtid]"},{"type":"entry","text":"collateral","headword":"collateral"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.平行的(side by side;parallel)：附属的(subordinate)：旁系的(having an"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka'laetaral]"},{"type":"text","text":"ancestor in common but descended from a diferent line) n. 担保品(property"},{"type":"text","text":"pledged by a borrower to protect the interests of the lender)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：col（共同）+later（边）+al→边挨着边的→平行的"},{"type":"entry","text":"incapacitate","headword":"incapacitate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.使无能力，使不适合（disable）"},{"type":"text","text":"[Inka'paesitert]"},{"type":"entry","text":"invariable","headword":"invariable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 恒定的，不变的(not changing or capable of change)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn'verariabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"changeless, consonant, equable, invariant"},{"type":"entry","text":"ultrasonic","headword":"ultrasonic"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad.超音速的，超声（波）的"},{"type":"text","text":"[Altra'sa:nrk]"},{"type":"entry","text":"touching","headword":"touching"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.动人的，感人的(moving);令人同情的(causing a feeling of pity or sympathy)"},{"type":"text","text":"['tatfrn]"},{"type":"entry","text":"overpowering","headword":"overpowering"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.压倒性的，不可抗拒的（overwhelming)"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvarpauarin]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自overpower(v压倒)"},{"type":"text","text":"Chariotte Salomon’s biography is a reminder that the currents of private life,"},{"type":"text","text":"however diverted, dislodged, or twisted by overpowering public events, retain"},{"type":"text","text":"their hold on the individual recording them."},{"type":"entry","text":"revert","headword":"revert"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.恢复，回复到(to go back to)：重新考虑(to talk about or consider again）"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'v3:rt]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：re（重新）+vert（转）→转回去→恢复"},{"type":"entry","text":"aptitude","headword":"aptitude"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.适宜(a natural tendency);才能，资质(a natural ability to do sth.)"},{"type":"text","text":"[aeptrtu:d]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：apt（能力）+itude（状态）→才能，资质"},{"type":"text","text":"aptitudefor有..方面的才能"}]},{"number":363,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"slimy","headword":"slimy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 黏滑的(of, relating to, or resembling slime)"},{"type":"text","text":"['slarmi]"},{"type":"text","text":"glutinous, miry, muddy, viscous"},{"type":"entry","text":"concentric","headword":"concentric"},{"type":"text","text":"adlj.同心的(having a common center)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan'sentrk]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：con（共同）+centr（中心）+ic→共同的中心→同心的"},{"type":"entry","text":"piousness","headword":"piousness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.虚诚"},{"type":"text","text":"['parasnas]"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自pious（adj虔诚的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"inoffensive","headword":"inoffensive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 无害的(causing no harm or injury); 不讨厌的(not objectionable to the"},{"type":"text","text":"[,Ina'fensiv]"},{"type":"text","text":"senses)"},{"type":"text","text":"Because medieval women's public participation in spiritual life was not"},{"type":"text","text":"welcomed by the male establishment, a compensating involvement with religious"},{"type":"example","text":"writings, inoffensive to the members of the establishment because of its privacy."},{"type":"text","text":"became important for many women."},{"type":"entry","text":"interlocking","headword":"interlocking"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj连锁的：关联的"},{"type":"text","text":"[intar'la:kin]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自interlock（v连锁：连接）"}]}]}